# ===========================================
# CeraUI Environment Configuration
# ===========================================
# You normally DO NOT need a root `.env`. The split is:
#
#   .env.development  — TRACKED, dev-only values (VITE_SOCKET_*, MOCK_SCENARIO).
#                       Loaded by Vite in `mode === "development"` and by the
#                       `pnpm dev` scripts (`dotenv -e .env.development`).
#   .env              — gitignored, loaded in EVERY Vite mode (incl. production).
#                       Leave it ABSENT. Anything here is also visible to a prod
#                       build, so it must never carry dev-only socket/mock values.
#   apps/frontend/.env.local — gitignored DEV-SYNC proxy overrides
#                              (see apps/frontend/.env.local.example).
#
# Production needs NO frontend socket config at all: the single backend binary
# serves the static frontend and the WebSocket RPC on the same origin, so the URL
# is derived from `window.location` and `VITE_SOCKET_*` are IGNORED in prod builds
# (see apps/frontend/src/lib/env/index.ts). A CI guard rejects any prod bundle that
# bakes a `ws://localhost` literal from a stray `.env`.

# -------------------------------------------
# Development socket overrides (dev only)
# -------------------------------------------
# These belong in `.env.development`, not here. Shown for reference only.
# VITE_SOCKET_ENDPOINT=ws://localhost   # scheme + host, no port
# VITE_SOCKET_PORT=3002                 # backend dev WebSocket port

# Brand configuration (CERALIVE or BELABOX)
# VITE_BRAND=CERALIVE

# -------------------------------------------
# Backend Configuration
# -------------------------------------------
# Backend HTTP/WS port. Optional — backend defaults apply when unset.
# PORT=3001

# NODE_ENV is NOT read from any env FILE: Vite sets the frontend mode itself
# (dev vs. `vite build`), and the backend `dev` scripts export
# `NODE_ENV=development` inline. Setting it in a file has no effect, so it is
# intentionally omitted.

# -------------------------------------------
# Mock System Configuration (Development Only)
# -------------------------------------------
# Simulated hardware for the Bun backend; lives in `.env.development`.
# Scenarios:
#   - single-modem    : 1 LTE modem, no WiFi, idle state
#   - multi-modem-wifi: 3 modems (4G/5G), WiFi enabled, hotspot capable
#   - streaming-active: 2 modems bonding, active stream, real-time stats
# MOCK_SCENARIO=multi-modem-wifi
